# Project Structure

## Top Level

```
index.html                 # Landing page — deployed to GitHub Pages with the PDFs
context/                   # Course-level reference documents
  SESSIONS.md              # Syllabus — session list, learning outcomes, schedule
  PROJECTS.md              # Project catalog — 30 projects with difficulty ratings
  DATASETS.md              # Dataset descriptions, sizes, access instructions
labs/                      # Lab handouts, one folder per session
  style.typ                # Shared document theme — imported by all labs
  1.1-single-node-benchmark/
    main.typ
  ...
sessions/                  # Slide decks, one folder per session
  style.typ                # Shared Touying/Metropolis theme — imported by all sessions
  1.1-introduction/
  1.2-distributed-systems/
  ...
```

- **`index.html`** — single-file landing page served via GitHub Pages. Uses Tailwind CDN for styling. Links to colocated PDFs in `build/`. Update it when sessions, labs, or datasets change.
- **`context/`** — course-level documents that describe the overall structure, projects, and datasets. These are reference material, not slides. Update them when the syllabus or project catalog changes.
- **`labs/`** — one folder per session containing a `main.typ` lab handout (objective, setup, walkthrough, takeaways). Lab folders are named to match their session number (e.g., `1.1-single-node-benchmark` for session 1.1). Not all sessions have a lab.
- **`sessions/style.typ`** — single source of truth for slide theme setup (Touying imports, Metropolis config, `dpas-theme` function). All session `main.typ` files import from here. Never duplicate theme configuration in individual sessions.
- **`labs/style.typ`** — single source of truth for lab document theme. All lab `main.typ` files import from here.
- Each session lives in its own folder under `sessions/`.

## Session Folder Layout

```
sessions/<session-name>/
  main.typ            # Assembly file — typst compile target
  assets/             # Images, diagrams, data files
  sections/           # Section files included by main.typ
    01-content.typ
    02-details.typ
    ...
```

- **`main.typ`** — the single entry point. Contains theme setup, metadata, and `#include` statements pulling in each section in order. This is the file passed to `typst compile`.
- **`assets/`** — all non-code resources (images, SVGs, diagrams). Referenced from sections via relative paths.
- **`sections/`** — one or more files per session, included in order by `main.typ`.

## Lab Folder Layout

```
labs/<lab-name>/
  main.typ            # Single document — the compile target
```

- **`main.typ`** — self-contained lab handout. Imports `../style.typ` for the document theme.

## Rules

- Never put slide content directly in `main.typ`. It only assembles.
- Assets are per-session. Do not reference assets from other sessions.
- When adding a new session or lab, also update `index.html` with the corresponding link.
